Mexican Stocks: America Movil, Penoles Shares Drop; Alfa Gains

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-05-04T20:31:36Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/mexican-stock-movers-alfa-sab-and-america-movil-sab-increase.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in Mexico trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m.  New York  time.  The IPC index fell 1 percent to 35,531.22.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA MM), the world’s largest producer of
aluminum engine heads for automobiles, rose 0.4 percent to
169.63 pesos as General Motors Co., an Alfa client and the
largest U.S. automaker, is expected to report tomorrow that
first-quarter earnings rose 63 percent to $1.74 billion,
according to the average of four analysts’ estimates compiled by
Bloomberg.  America Movil  SAB (AMXL MM), the wireless carrier
controlled by billionaire  Carlos Slim , declined 2.7 percent to
30.66 pesos after Mexico’s  Supreme Court  ruled that the
country’s telephone companies cannot use a legal procedure to
protect themselves from price cuts ordered by the government.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM),  Mexico ’s largest
silver producer, retreated 4.3 percent to 412.06 pesos. Silver
futures for July delivery tumbled as much as $3.65, or 8.6
percent, to $38.94 an ounce on the Comex in New York.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
 llazaroff@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
